  "texts": [
    "• Most studies have predicted student outcomes at the end of the course, whereas few studies applied early predictions.",
    "Therefore, developing a hybrid model that combines the early and end-of-course prediction can help in timely intervention.",
    "• Most studies have used student's learning behavior and activity features for prediction, whereas few studies have employed demographic, previous, and current academic features along with learning behavior and activity features.",
    "Therefore, there is a need for conducting more research that considers combining academic and learning behavior and activity features, to discover significant learning patterns and understand the student's needs.",
    "Studies on predicting student's academic performance have been developed in recent years to help both administrators and instructors enhance the teaching and learning process."
